    <title type="html"><![CDATA[RubyPlayer-0.6.0 has been released]]></title>
    <link href="http://flipback.github.com/ruby-player/blog/2012/06/17/rubyplayer-0-dot-6-0-has-been-released/"/>
    <updated>2012-06-17T21:17:00+06:00</updated>
    <id>http://flipback.github.com/ruby-player/blog/2012/06/17/rubyplayer-0-dot-6-0-has-been-released</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;m glad to report about a new minor release of <strong>RubyPlayer</strong>. Now you can subscribe interfaces with
shorter syntax:</p>

<figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="nb">require</span> <span class="s1">&#39;ruby-player&#39;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="no">Player</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="no">Client</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">connect</span> <span class="s2">&quot;localhost&quot;</span> <span class="k">do</span> <span class="o">|</span><span class="n">robot</span><span class="o">|</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="c1"># subscribe to :ranger interface (default index=0)</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">ranger</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">robot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ranger</span> <span class="c1"># Instead of robot.subscribe(:ranger)</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="c1"># or with index</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">ranger</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">robot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ranger</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># Instead of robot.subscribe(:ranger, index: 2)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>




<!-- more -->


<p>The library supports <a href="http://playerstage.sourceforge.net/doc/Player-svn/player/group__interface__aio.html">aio</a> interface
for analog I\O since this version:</p>

<figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">aio</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">robot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">aio</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">aio</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">voltages</span> <span class="c1">#=&gt; [0.2, 0.6, 0.7] - Voltages from 0 to 5 V</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">aio</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="o">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">3</span> <span class="c1"># Set voltage on #1 output</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Also I have cleaned code and deleted all deprecated methods.</p>

<p>Regards, <a href="https://github.com/flipback">@flipback</a>.</p>
]]></content>
